## Premiere Pro ExtendScript - Bins and Project Organization

### Key Objects and Methods:

1. **`app.project.rootItem`** - The root of the project panel, where all items and bins are stored

2. **`createBin(name)`** - Method to create a new bin (folder) within the project
   ```javascript
   var newBin = app.project.rootItem.createBin("My New Bin");
   ```

3. **`projectItem`** - Represents any item in the project (clips, sequences, bins)
   - Properties include: `name`, `type`, `treePath`, `children`

4. **`moveBin(destination)`** - Move a bin to another location in the project

5. **`findItemsMatchingMediaPath()`** - Find items based on their file path

### Example - Creating Organized Folder Structure:
```javascript
var rootBin = app.project.rootItem;
var footageBin = rootBin.createBin("Footage");
var audioBin = rootBin.createBin("Audio");
var graphicsBin = rootBin.createBin("Graphics");

// Create nested bins
var bRollBin = footageBin.createBin("B-Roll");
```

### Iterating Through Project Items:
```javascript
for (var i = 0; i < app.project.rootItem.children.numItems; i++) {
    var item = app.project.rootItem.children[i];
    $.writeln(item.name + " - Type: " + item.type);
}
```

